obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `THE DAKSHINA BHARAT HINDI PRACHAR SABHA ACT, 1964`
  line `A CT N O. 14 OF 1964`
  line `[12 th May, 1964. ]`
  line `An Act to declare the institution known as the Dakshina Bharat Hindi Prachar Sabha, having at`
  line `present its registered office at Madras, to be an institution of national importance and to`
  line `provide for certain matters connected therewith.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Fifteenth year of t he Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `1. Short title and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Dakshina Bharat Hindi Prachar`
  line `Sabha Act, 196 4.`
  line `( 2 ) I t shall come into force on such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ memorandum ” means the memorandum of association of the Sabha filed with the Registrar`
  line `of Joint Stock Companies, Madras, under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860);`
  line `( b ) “ rules and regulations ” includes any rule or regulation, by whatever name called, which the`
  line `Sabha is competent to make in the exercise of the powers conferred on it under the Societies`
  line `Registration Act, 1860, but shall not include any bye - laws or standing orders made under the rules`
  line `and regulations for the conduct of its work;`
  line `( c ) “ Sabha ” means the Da kshina Bharat Hindi Prachar Sabha registered under the Societies`
  line `Registration Act, 1860.`
  line `3. Declaration of the Dakshina Bharat Hindi Prachar Sabha as an institution of national`
  line `importance. — Whereas the objects of the institution known as the Dakshina Bharat Hindi Prachar`
  line `Sabha are such as to make it an institution of national importance, it is hereby declared that the Dakshina`
  line `Bharat Hindi Prachar Sabha is an institution of national importance.`
  line `4. Grant of degrees, diplomas and certificates by the Sabha. — Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in the University Grants Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956), or in any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, the Sabha may hold such examinations and grant such degrees, diplomas and certificates for`
  line `proficiency in the Hindi or in the teaching of Hindi as may be determined by the Sabha from time to time.`
  line `5. Accounts and A udit. — ( 1 ) The Sabha shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the balance - sheet in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) The accounts of the Sabha shall, once at least in every year, be audited by a chartered accountant`
  line `in practice within the meaning of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949), to be appointed`
  line `annually by the Sabha:`
  line `Provided that no member of the Sabha who is a chartered acc ountant or a person who is in`
  line `partnership with such member, shall be eligible for appointment as an auditor under this section.`
  line `( 3 ) Every auditor shall, in the performance of his duties, have at all reasonable times access to the`
  line `registers, books of accoun t, records and other documents of the Sabha or of any committee, council,`
  line `board or branch of the Sabha.`
  line `( 4 ) As soon as may be practicable at the end of each year, the auditors shall submit their report to the`
  line `Sabha and shall also forward a copy thereof to the Central Government for its information.`
  line `1. 1st June, 1964, vide notification No. S.O. 1898, dated 30th May, 1964, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3( ii ).`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
