obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `6. Prior approval of the Central Government necessary for certain action by the Sabha. —`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860), or in the`
  line `memorandum or rules and regulations, the Sabha shall not, except with the previous appro val of the`
  line `Central Government, —`
  line `( a ) alter, extend or abridge any of the purposes for which it has been established or for which it is`
  line `being used immediately before the commencement of this Act, or amalgamate itself, either wholly or`
  line `partially, with any other institution or society; or`
  line `( b ) alter or amend in any manner the m emorandum or rules and regulations; or`
  line `( c ) be dissolved.`
  line `7. Review of work done, etc. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may constitute, after consultation with`
  line `the Sabha, one or more committees consisting of such number of persons as it thinks fit to appoint thereto`
  line `for all or any of the following purposes, namely: —`
  line `( a ) reviewing the work done by the Sabha during any specified period and the progress made by`
  line `it; and`
  line `( b ) evaluating the work done by the Sabha.`
  line `( 2 ) The Sabha shall afford all necessary facilities to any committee constituted under sub - section ( 1 )`
  line `for the purpose of enabling it to carry out its duties.`
  line `( 3 ) The report of any committee constituted under sub - section ( 1 ) shall be submitted to the Central`
  line `Government within such time and in such manner as that Government may direct.`
  line `( 4 ) The Sabha shall be entitled to appoint a representative who shall have the right to be present and`
  line `to be heard at such review or evaluation.`
  line `( 5 ) The Central Government may address the P resident of the Sabha with reference t o the result of`
  line `such review or evaluation as disclosed in the report of any committee constituted under sub - section ( 1 ),`
  line `and the President of the Sabha shall communicate to the Central Government the action, if any, taken`
  line thereon.
  line `( 6 ) When the Central Gove rnment has, in pursuance of sub - section ( 5 ), addressed the P resident of the`
  line `Sabha in connection with any matter and the President of the Sabha does not within a reasonable time`
  line `take action to the satisfaction of the Central Government in respect thereof, t he Central Government may,`
  line `after allowing the Sabha an opportunity of furnishing explanations or making representations, issue such`
  line `directions as that Government considers necessary in respect of any of the matters dealt with in the report`
  line `and the Sabha shall notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force or in the`
  line `memorandum or rules and regulations of the Sabha, comply with such directions.`
  line `( 7 ) The members of any committee constituted under sub - section ( 1 ) shall be paid such allowances as`
  line `the Central Government may, by order, fix and such allowances together with the expenses incurred, with`
  line `the previous approval of the Central Government, by any such committee in the performance of its`
  line `functions (including any salary, remunera tions or allowances, if any, payable to any person employed by`
  line `any such committee), shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force or`
  line `in the memorandum or rules and regulations of the Sabha, be paid out of the funds of the Sabha.`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
